{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01P6JwxCjeC1ZqssWAPF2Mwe","type":"tool_result","content":"# Next.js Auth.js Installation with App Router\n\n## Installation Command\n```\nnpm install next-auth@beta\n```\n\nAlternative package managers:\n- `pnpm add next-auth@beta`\n- `yarn add next-auth@beta`\n- `bun add next-auth@beta`\n\n## Environment Setup\nGenerate the required `AUTH_SECRET`:\n```\nnpx auth secret\n```\n\nThis automatically adds it to your `.env.local` file.\n\n## Configuration File (auth.ts)\n\nCreate `./auth.ts` at your project root:\n\n```typescript\nimport NextAuth from \"next-auth\"\n\nexport const { handlers, signIn, signOut, auth } = NextAuth({\n  providers: [],\n})\n```\n\n## API Route Handler\n\nCreate `./app/api/auth/[...nextauth]/route.ts`:\n\n```typescript\nimport { handlers } from \"@/auth\"\nexport const { GET, POST } = handlers\n```\n\n## Session Management (Optional Proxy)\n\nCreate `./proxy.ts`:\n\n```typescript\nexport { auth as proxy } from \"@/auth\"\n```\n\n**Note:** For Next.js 16+, use `proxy.ts`. For earlier versions, use `middleware.ts` with `export { auth as middleware }`.\n\nThe documentation indicates this setup provides \"the basic setup is complete\" before adding authentication providers to the `providers` array."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"4c220b3b-cbe4-4615-939a-f8ccaabf4974","uuid":"b389b227-2496-4d0e-9787-7493fda2e0cc","tool_use_result":{"bytes":183068,"code":200,"codeText":"OK","result":"# Next.js Auth.js Installation with App Router\n\n## Installation Command\n```\nnpm install next-auth@beta\n```\n\nAlternative package managers:\n- `pnpm add next-auth@beta`\n- `yarn add next-auth@beta`\n- `bun add next-auth@beta`\n\n## Environment Setup\nGenerate the required `AUTH_SECRET`:\n```\nnpx auth secret\n```\n\nThis automatically adds it to your `.env.local` file.\n\n## Configuration File (auth.ts)\n\nCreate `./auth.ts` at your project root:\n\n```typescript\nimport NextAuth from \"next-auth\"\n\nexport const { handlers, signIn, signOut, auth } = NextAuth({\n  providers: [],\n})\n```\n\n## API Route Handler\n\nCreate `./app/api/auth/[...nextauth]/route.ts`:\n\n```typescript\nimport { handlers } from \"@/auth\"\nexport const { GET, POST } = handlers\n```\n\n## Session Management (Optional Proxy)\n\nCreate `./proxy.ts`:\n\n```typescript\nexport { auth as proxy } from \"@/auth\"\n```\n\n**Note:** For Next.js 16+, use `proxy.ts`. For earlier versions, use `middleware.ts` with `export { auth as middleware }`.\n\nThe documentation indicates this setup provides \"the basic setup is complete\" before adding authentication providers to the `providers` array.","durationMs":6082,"url":"https://authjs.dev/getting-started/installation"}}
