{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01QgNwNVSnDPqGLAi5czx65R","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01PfQYbiL8gtLQaYf57Trv78","name":"Edit","input":{"replace_all":false,"file_path":"/home/jorgecevallos/Documents/web-video/.ralph-tui/progress.md","old_string":"- **Next.js 16 + ESLint**: `next lint` CLI command was removed in Next.js 16. Use `eslint .` directly with flat config. `eslint-config-next@16` exports a flat config array natively — no need for `@eslint/eslintrc` FlatCompat wrapper.","new_string":"- **NextAuth.js v5 (Auth.js)**: Install with `pnpm add next-auth@beta`. Config in `auth.ts` at project root. API route at `app/api/auth/[...nextauth]/route.ts`. SessionProvider wraps app in layout. For Next.js 16, use `proxy.ts` instead of `middleware.ts` for route protection. GitHub provider auto-reads `AUTH_GITHUB_ID` and `AUTH_GITHUB_SECRET` env vars.\n- **Next.js 16 + ESLint**: `next lint` CLI command was removed in Next.js 16. Use `eslint .` directly with flat config. `eslint-config-next@16` exports a flat config array natively — no need for `@eslint/eslintrc` FlatCompat wrapper."},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":291,"cache_read_input_tokens":51663,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":291},"output_tokens":25,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"4c220b3b-cbe4-4615-939a-f8ccaabf4974","uuid":"621287d6-b164-4863-a64a-be029c0de941"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01PfQYbiL8gtLQaYf57Trv78","type":"tool_result","content":"The file /home/jorgecevallos/Documents/web-video/.ralph-tui/progress.md has been updated successfully."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"4c220b3b-cbe4-4615-939a-f8ccaabf4974","uuid":"367ad795-210c-4348-833e-a37deccf9c88","tool_use_result":{"filePath":"/home/jorgecevallos/Documents/web-video/.ralph-tui/progress.md","oldString":"- **Next.js 16 + ESLint**: `next lint` CLI command was removed in Next.js 16. Use `eslint .` directly with flat config. `eslint-config-next@16` exports a flat config array natively — no need for `@eslint/eslintrc` FlatCompat wrapper.","newString":"- **NextAuth.js v5 (Auth.js)**: Install with `pnpm add next-auth@beta`. Config in `auth.ts` at project root. API route at `app/api/auth/[...nextauth]/route.ts`. SessionProvider wraps app in layout. For Next.js 16, use `proxy.ts` instead of `middleware.ts` for route protection. GitHub provider auto-reads `AUTH_GITHUB_ID` and `AUTH_GITHUB_SECRET` env vars.\n- **Next.js 16 + ESLint**: `next lint` CLI command was removed in Next.js 16. Use `eslint .` directly with flat config. `eslint-config-next@16` exports a flat config array natively — no need for `@eslint/eslintrc` FlatCompat wrapper.","originalFile":"# Ralph Progress Log\n\nThis file tracks progress across iterations. Agents update this file\nafter each iteration and it's included in prompts for context.\n\n## Codebase Patterns (Study These First)\n\n- **Next.js 16 + ESLint**: `next lint` CLI command was removed in Next.js 16. Use `eslint .` directly with flat config. `eslint-config-next@16` exports a flat config array natively — no need for `@eslint/eslintrc` FlatCompat wrapper.\n- **Tailwind CSS v4**: Uses `@import \"tailwindcss\"` and `@theme {}` blocks in CSS instead of `tailwind.config.js`. Custom colors defined via `--color-*` CSS variables in `@theme`.\n- **Custom colors**: Access via `text-text-primary`, `bg-background`, `bg-accent`, etc. (Tailwind v4 maps `--color-*` to utility classes automatically).\n- **Font**: Inter loaded via `next/font/google` with `variable: \"--font-inter\"`, applied to `<html>` class. CSS uses `--font-sans` in `@theme` block.\n- **Package manager**: pnpm installed at `$HOME/.local/bin/pnpm` (nix store is read-only). Always `export PATH=\"$HOME/.local/bin:$PATH\"` before pnpm commands.\n\n---\n\n## 2026-02-17 - web-video-l39.1\n- Initialized Next.js 16 project with TypeScript, App Router, Tailwind CSS v4, ESLint 9\n- Configured dark theme with custom color palette (background #0a0a0a, surface #141414, accent purple #6d28d9)\n- Set up Inter font via next/font/google\n- Created base layout (app/layout.tsx) with dark background, text colors, and antialiased rendering\n- Created placeholder home page (app/page.tsx) with hero-like content\n- Created folder structure: app/, components/, lib/\n- **Files changed:**\n  - `package.json` - scripts, dependencies\n  - `tsconfig.json` - TypeScript config (auto-updated by Next.js)\n  - `next.config.ts` - Next.js config\n  - `postcss.config.mjs` - PostCSS with @tailwindcss/postcss\n  - `eslint.config.mjs` - ESLint flat config with eslint-config-next\n  - `app/globals.css` - Tailwind v4 theme with custom dark colors\n  - `app/layout.tsx` - Root layout with Inter font and dark theme\n  - `app/page.tsx` - Home page placeholder\n  - `.gitignore` - Standard Next.js gitignore\n- **Learnings:**\n  - Next.js 16 removed the `next lint` CLI command; use `eslint .` directly\n  - `eslint-config-next@16` exports flat config natively, no FlatCompat needed\n  - Tailwind CSS v4 uses `@theme {}` blocks instead of `tailwind.config.js`\n  - pnpm can't be installed globally in nix — use `--prefix=$HOME/.local`\n  - `create-next-app` refuses to run in non-empty directories; manual setup is more reliable\n---\n\n## 2026-02-17 - web-video-l39.2\n- Created Hero section component (`components/Hero.tsx`) with title, accent-colored keyword, subtitle, and CTA button\n- Updated `app/page.tsx` to import and render the Hero component with a `#compresor` anchor placeholder\n- Hero is fully responsive (text scales from `text-4xl` on mobile to `text-6xl` on desktop)\n- CTA button uses `<a href=\"#compresor\">` to scroll to the future compressor section\n- **Files changed:**\n  - `components/Hero.tsx` - New Hero section component\n  - `app/page.tsx` - Updated to use Hero component\n- **Learnings:**\n  - The `@/` path alias works out of the box with Next.js 16 + TypeScript for importing from project root\n  - Using `text-accent-light` for keyword emphasis works well with the existing theme palette\n---\n\n## 2026-02-17 - web-video-l39.4\n- Created `VideoUpload` component (`components/VideoUpload.tsx`) with drag & drop and click-to-select functionality\n- Component validates file types against both MIME types and file extensions for robustness\n- Displays file name, size (formatted), and format after selection\n- Error message shown when non-video file is selected\n- Created `CompressorSection` wrapper component (`components/CompressorSection.tsx`) as client component to manage upload state\n- Updated `app/page.tsx` to replace placeholder anchor with `CompressorSection`\n- **Files changed:**\n  - `components/VideoUpload.tsx` - New video upload component with drag & drop\n  - `components/CompressorSection.tsx` - New client wrapper for the compressor section\n  - `app/page.tsx` - Replaced placeholder anchor with CompressorSection\n- **Learnings:**\n  - Client components (`\"use client\"`) are needed for drag & drop and file input state management in Next.js App Router\n  - Wrapping interactive sections in a dedicated client component (CompressorSection) keeps the page.tsx as a server component\n  - The `SelectedFile` interface is exported for reuse by future components (US-005 compression input)\n  - Tailwind v4 custom colors work with opacity modifiers (e.g., `bg-accent/10`, `bg-accent/15`) out of the box\n  - Dual validation (MIME type + extension) handles edge cases where browsers report different MIME types for the same format\n---\n\n## 2026-02-17 - web-video-l39.5\n- Added target size input (MB) with validation to `CompressorSection`\n- Validations: minimum 1 MB, must be less than original file size, numeric input\n- Created API route `app/api/compress/route.ts` using `fluent-ffmpeg` for server-side compression\n- API route calculates video bitrate from target size and video duration (reserves 128kbps for audio)\n- Compression uses single-pass encoding with `-movflags +faststart` for web-optimized output\n- Added spinner animation on compress button during compression\n- Added animated progress bar indicator during compression\n- Error state with retry button and descriptive error messages\n- Success state shows compressed size vs original, download button, and \"compress another\" reset\n- Download generates descriptive filename (e.g., `video_compressed_9.00mb.mp4`)\n- Configured `next.config.ts` with `serverExternalPackages: [\"fluent-ffmpeg\"]` for proper server-side usage\n- Installed `fluent-ffmpeg` + `@types/fluent-ffmpeg` dependencies\n- **Files changed:**\n  - `components/CompressorSection.tsx` - Added target size input, compress button, progress, error/success states\n  - `app/api/compress/route.ts` - New API route for server-side FFmpeg compression\n  - `next.config.ts` - Added `serverExternalPackages` for fluent-ffmpeg\n  - `package.json` - Added fluent-ffmpeg dependency and @types/fluent-ffmpeg dev dependency\n- **Learnings:**\n  - `fluent-ffmpeg` is deprecated but still functional; it's the most common Node.js FFmpeg wrapper\n  - Next.js App Router API routes use `formData()` on the request to handle file uploads natively (no body-parser config needed)\n  - `serverExternalPackages` in next.config.ts is needed to prevent Next.js from bundling native/CLI-dependent packages like fluent-ffmpeg\n  - Bitrate calculation: `videoBitrate = (targetSizeBytes * 8 - audioBitrate * duration) / duration` — must subtract audio bits from total budget\n  - Streaming response with `ReadableStream` from `createReadStream` works well for returning large files from API routes\n  - Custom headers like `X-Compressed-Size` can be read client-side from `response.headers.get()` for metadata about the result\n---\n\n## 2026-02-17 - web-video-l39.3\n- Created `Features` component (`components/Features.tsx`) with 4 feature cards in a responsive grid\n- Features: sin límite de tamaño, todos los formatos, tamaño exacto, 100% gratis\n- Each card has an inline SVG icon (Heroicons), title, and description\n- Cards use dark theme: `bg-surface`, `border-border`, hover to `bg-surface-hover`/`border-border-hover`\n- Icon container uses `bg-accent/10` with `text-accent-light` for purple accent\n- Responsive grid: 1 col mobile, 2 col `sm`, 4 col `lg`\n- Updated `app/page.tsx` to render Features between Hero and CompressorSection\n- **Files changed:**\n  - `components/Features.tsx` - New features/benefits section component\n  - `app/page.tsx` - Added Features import and rendering\n- **Learnings:**\n  - Inline SVGs from Heroicons work cleanly in React/Next.js without extra dependencies\n  - The existing theme palette (`surface`, `border`, `accent/10`, `accent-light`) provides all needed tokens for card components\n---\n\n## 2026-02-17 - web-video-l39.6\n- US-006 (Download of compressed video) was already fully implemented during US-005 iteration\n- All acceptance criteria verified as present in `components/CompressorSection.tsx`:\n  - Download button visible after compression (line 269-275)\n  - Descriptive filename: `{baseName}_compressed_{sizeMB}mb.mp4` (line 72)\n  - Compressed file size displayed with comparison to original (lines 259-266)\n  - \"Comprimir otro\" reset button resets all state (lines 276-282, handleReset)\n- Quality gates pass: `pnpm typecheck` and `pnpm lint` both succeed\n- **Files changed:** None (already complete)\n- **Learnings:**\n  - US-005 implemented download functionality as part of the compression flow, making US-006 a no-op\n  - The `handleDownload` pattern using `URL.createObjectURL` + programmatic `<a>` click is the standard browser download approach\n---\n\n## 2026-02-17 - web-video-l39.7\n- Created FAQ accordion component (`components/FAQ.tsx`) with 6 collapsible questions\n- Questions cover: formatos soportados, límites de tamaño, privacidad, calidad, formato de salida, necesidad de cuenta\n- Smooth expand/collapse animation using CSS `grid-rows-[0fr]`/`grid-rows-[1fr]` trick with `transition-all`\n- Chevron icon rotates 180° on open with `transition-transform`\n- Single-open behavior (clicking one closes the previously open item)\n- Dark theme consistent: `bg-surface`, `border-border`, `hover:bg-surface-hover`\n- Updated `app/page.tsx` to render FAQ between CompressorSection and future Footer\n- **Files changed:**\n  - `components/FAQ.tsx` - New FAQ accordion component\n  - `app/page.tsx` - Added FAQ import and rendering\n- **Learnings:**\n  - CSS `grid-rows-[0fr]`/`grid-rows-[1fr]` with `overflow-hidden` child is the cleanest pure-CSS accordion animation approach — no JS height measurement needed\n  - Tailwind v4 arbitrary values like `grid-rows-[0fr]` work seamlessly for this pattern\n  - `divide-y divide-border` on the container cleanly handles separator lines between accordion items\n---\n\n## 2026-02-17 - web-video-l39.8\n- Created Footer component (`components/Footer.tsx`) with minimalist design\n- Footer includes dynamic copyright year, privacy and contact links\n- Uses `border-t border-border` and `bg-surface/50` for subtle visual separation\n- Responsive layout: stacked on mobile, horizontal on desktop (`sm:flex-row`)\n- Updated `app/page.tsx` to render Footer outside `<main>` using a fragment wrapper\n- **Files changed:**\n  - `components/Footer.tsx` - New footer component\n  - `app/page.tsx` - Added Footer import and rendering, wrapped in fragment\n- **Learnings:**\n  - `bg-surface/50` (opacity modifier) creates a subtle background that differentiates the footer from the main content without being too prominent\n  - Footer is placed outside `<main>` for semantic HTML — it's a sibling, not a child of main content\n---\n","structuredPatch":[{"oldStart":5,"oldLines":6,"newStart":5,"newLines":7,"lines":[" "," ## Codebase Patterns (Study These First)"," ","+- **NextAuth.js v5 (Auth.js)**: Install with `pnpm add next-auth@beta`. Config in `auth.ts` at project root. API route at `app/api/auth/[...nextauth]/route.ts`. SessionProvider wraps app in layout. For Next.js 16, use `proxy.ts` instead of `middleware.ts` for route protection. GitHub provider auto-reads `AUTH_GITHUB_ID` and `AUTH_GITHUB_SECRET` env vars."," - **Next.js 16 + ESLint**: `next lint` CLI command was removed in Next.js 16. Use `eslint .` directly with flat config. `eslint-config-next@16` exports a flat config array natively — no need for `@eslint/eslintrc` FlatCompat wrapper."," - **Tailwind CSS v4**: Uses `@import \"tailwindcss\"` and `@theme {}` blocks in CSS instead of `tailwind.config.js`. Custom colors defined via `--color-*` CSS variables in `@theme`."," - **Custom colors**: Access via `text-text-primary`, `bg-background`, `bg-accent`, etc. (Tailwind v4 maps `--color-*` to utility classes automatically)."]}],"userModified":false,"replaceAll":false}}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01LuHufqV29zE3q6GY5eG52C","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01PkauAPeiZRdMxkFGuUmjyR","name":"Edit","input":{"replace_all":false,"file_path":"/home/jorgecevallos/Documents/web-video/.ralph-tui/progress.md","old_string":"  - Footer is placed outside `<main>` for semantic HTML — it's a sibling, not a child of main content\n---","new_string":"  - Footer is placed outside `<main>` for semantic HTML — it's a sibling, not a child of main content\n---\n\n## 2026-02-17 - web-video-l39.9\n- Implemented optional login with NextAuth.js v5 (Auth.js) using GitHub as OAuth provider\n- Created `auth.ts` root config file exporting `handlers`, `signIn`, `signOut`, `auth`\n- Created `app/api/auth/[...nextauth]/route.ts` API route for auth handlers\n- Created `components/SessionProvider.tsx` client wrapper for NextAuthSessionProvider\n- Created `components/Header.tsx` with login button (unauthenticated), avatar+name+logout (authenticated), and loading skeleton\n- Updated `app/layout.tsx` to wrap children with SessionProvider, added Header and `pt-14` padding for fixed header\n- Updated `next.config.ts` with `images.remotePatterns` for GitHub and Google avatar domains\n- Created `.env.local` with `AUTH_SECRET` and placeholder GitHub OAuth credentials\n- Compressor works without login — no auth gates on any compression functionality\n- **Files changed:**\n  - `auth.ts` - New NextAuth v5 root configuration with GitHub provider\n  - `app/api/auth/[...nextauth]/route.ts` - New API route for auth handlers\n  - `components/SessionProvider.tsx` - New client-side session provider wrapper\n  - `components/Header.tsx` - New header with login/logout and session state\n  - `app/layout.tsx` - Added SessionProvider, Header, and content padding\n  - `next.config.ts` - Added image remote patterns for avatar domains\n  - `.env.local` - Auth secrets and GitHub OAuth placeholders (gitignored)\n  - `package.json` / `pnpm-lock.yaml` - Added next-auth@5.0.0-beta.30\n- **Learnings:**\n  - `next-auth@beta` (v5) installs cleanly with pnpm on Next.js 16 without peer dep issues\n  - GitHub provider in Auth.js v5 auto-reads `AUTH_GITHUB_ID` and `AUTH_GITHUB_SECRET` environment variables — no explicit `clientId`/`clientSecret` config needed\n  - `SessionProvider` must be a client component wrapping the layout's children for `useSession` to work in child client components\n  - Fixed header with `backdrop-blur-md` and `bg-background/80` creates a clean glassmorphism effect over dark theme\n  - `pt-14` on content div compensates for the fixed header height (~56px)\n  - `next/image` requires `remotePatterns` config for external avatar URLs (GitHub: `avatars.githubusercontent.com`, Google: `lh3.googleusercontent.com`)\n---"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":435,"cache_read_input_tokens":51954,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":435},"output_tokens":25,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"4c220b3b-cbe4-4615-939a-f8ccaabf4974","uuid":"657e6d9d-c488-4450-8e66-c56467ae53bb"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01PkauAPeiZRdMxkFGuUmjyR","type":"tool_result","content":"The file /home/jorgecevallos/Documents/web-video/.ralph-tui/progress.md has been updated successfully."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"4c220b3b-cbe4-4615-939a-f8ccaabf4974","uuid":"8f3243e0-a8bd-4482-a74c-73b61428b2cb","tool_use_result":{"filePath":"/home/jorgecevallos/Documents/web-video/.ralph-tui/progress.md","oldString":"  - Footer is placed outside `<main>` for semantic HTML — it's a sibling, not a child of main content\n---","newString":"  - Footer is placed outside `<main>` for semantic HTML — it's a sibling, not a child of main content\n---\n\n## 2026-02-17 - web-video-l39.9\n- Implemented optional login with NextAuth.js v5 (Auth.js) using GitHub as OAuth provider\n- Created `auth.ts` root config file exporting `handlers`, `signIn`, `signOut`, `auth`\n- Created `app/api/auth/[...nextauth]/route.ts` API route for auth handlers\n- Created `components/SessionProvider.tsx` client wrapper for NextAuthSessionProvider\n- Created `components/Header.tsx` with login button (unauthenticated), avatar+name+logout (authenticated), and loading skeleton\n- Updated `app/layout.tsx` to wrap children with SessionProvider, added Header and `pt-14` padding for fixed header\n- Updated `next.config.ts` with `images.remotePatterns` for GitHub and Google avatar domains\n- Created `.env.local` with `AUTH_SECRET` and placeholder GitHub OAuth credentials\n- Compressor works without login — no auth gates on any compression functionality\n- **Files changed:**\n  - `auth.ts` - New NextAuth v5 root configuration with GitHub provider\n  - `app/api/auth/[...nextauth]/route.ts` - New API route for auth handlers\n  - `components/SessionProvider.tsx` - New client-side session provider wrapper\n  - `components/Header.tsx` - New header with login/logout and session state\n  - `app/layout.tsx` - Added SessionProvider, Header, and content padding\n  - `next.config.ts` - Added image remote patterns for avatar domains\n  - `.env.local` - Auth secrets and GitHub OAuth placeholders (gitignored)\n  - `package.json` / `pnpm-lock.yaml` - Added next-auth@5.0.0-beta.30\n- **Learnings:**\n  - `next-auth@beta` (v5) installs cleanly with pnpm on Next.js 16 without peer dep issues\n  - GitHub provider in Auth.js v5 auto-reads `AUTH_GITHUB_ID` and `AUTH_GITHUB_SECRET` environment variables — no explicit `clientId`/`clientSecret` config needed\n  - `SessionProvider` must be a client component wrapping the layout's children for `useSession` to work in child client components\n  - Fixed header with `backdrop-blur-md` and `bg-background/80` creates a clean glassmorphism effect over dark theme\n  - `pt-14` on content div compensates for the fixed header height (~56px)\n  - `next/image` requires `remotePatterns` config for external avatar URLs (GitHub: `avatars.githubusercontent.com`, Google: `lh3.googleusercontent.com`)\n---","originalFile":"# Ralph Progress Log\n\nThis file tracks progress across iterations. Agents update this file\nafter each iteration and it's included in prompts for context.\n\n## Codebase Patterns (Study These First)\n\n- **NextAuth.js v5 (Auth.js)**: Install with `pnpm add next-auth@beta`. Config in `auth.ts` at project root. API route at `app/api/auth/[...nextauth]/route.ts`. SessionProvider wraps app in layout. For Next.js 16, use `proxy.ts` instead of `middleware.ts` for route protection. GitHub provider auto-reads `AUTH_GITHUB_ID` and `AUTH_GITHUB_SECRET` env vars.\n- **Next.js 16 + ESLint**: `next lint` CLI command was removed in Next.js 16. Use `eslint .` directly with flat config. `eslint-config-next@16` exports a flat config array natively — no need for `@eslint/eslintrc` FlatCompat wrapper.\n- **Tailwind CSS v4**: Uses `@import \"tailwindcss\"` and `@theme {}` blocks in CSS instead of `tailwind.config.js`. Custom colors defined via `--color-*` CSS variables in `@theme`.\n- **Custom colors**: Access via `text-text-primary`, `bg-background`, `bg-accent`, etc. (Tailwind v4 maps `--color-*` to utility classes automatically).\n- **Font**: Inter loaded via `next/font/google` with `variable: \"--font-inter\"`, applied to `<html>` class. CSS uses `--font-sans` in `@theme` block.\n- **Package manager**: pnpm installed at `$HOME/.local/bin/pnpm` (nix store is read-only). Always `export PATH=\"$HOME/.local/bin:$PATH\"` before pnpm commands.\n\n---\n\n## 2026-02-17 - web-video-l39.1\n- Initialized Next.js 16 project with TypeScript, App Router, Tailwind CSS v4, ESLint 9\n- Configured dark theme with custom color palette (background #0a0a0a, surface #141414, accent purple #6d28d9)\n- Set up Inter font via next/font/google\n- Created base layout (app/layout.tsx) with dark background, text colors, and antialiased rendering\n- Created placeholder home page (app/page.tsx) with hero-like content\n- Created folder structure: app/, components/, lib/\n- **Files changed:**\n  - `package.json` - scripts, dependencies\n  - `tsconfig.json` - TypeScript config (auto-updated by Next.js)\n  - `next.config.ts` - Next.js config\n  - `postcss.config.mjs` - PostCSS with @tailwindcss/postcss\n  - `eslint.config.mjs` - ESLint flat config with eslint-config-next\n  - `app/globals.css` - Tailwind v4 theme with custom dark colors\n  - `app/layout.tsx` - Root layout with Inter font and dark theme\n  - `app/page.tsx` - Home page placeholder\n  - `.gitignore` - Standard Next.js gitignore\n- **Learnings:**\n  - Next.js 16 removed the `next lint` CLI command; use `eslint .` directly\n  - `eslint-config-next@16` exports flat config natively, no FlatCompat needed\n  - Tailwind CSS v4 uses `@theme {}` blocks instead of `tailwind.config.js`\n  - pnpm can't be installed globally in nix — use `--prefix=$HOME/.local`\n  - `create-next-app` refuses to run in non-empty directories; manual setup is more reliable\n---\n\n## 2026-02-17 - web-video-l39.2\n- Created Hero section component (`components/Hero.tsx`) with title, accent-colored keyword, subtitle, and CTA button\n- Updated `app/page.tsx` to import and render the Hero component with a `#compresor` anchor placeholder\n- Hero is fully responsive (text scales from `text-4xl` on mobile to `text-6xl` on desktop)\n- CTA button uses `<a href=\"#compresor\">` to scroll to the future compressor section\n- **Files changed:**\n  - `components/Hero.tsx` - New Hero section component\n  - `app/page.tsx` - Updated to use Hero component\n- **Learnings:**\n  - The `@/` path alias works out of the box with Next.js 16 + TypeScript for importing from project root\n  - Using `text-accent-light` for keyword emphasis works well with the existing theme palette\n---\n\n## 2026-02-17 - web-video-l39.4\n- Created `VideoUpload` component (`components/VideoUpload.tsx`) with drag & drop and click-to-select functionality\n- Component validates file types against both MIME types and file extensions for robustness\n- Displays file name, size (formatted), and format after selection\n- Error message shown when non-video file is selected\n- Created `CompressorSection` wrapper component (`components/CompressorSection.tsx`) as client component to manage upload state\n- Updated `app/page.tsx` to replace placeholder anchor with `CompressorSection`\n- **Files changed:**\n  - `components/VideoUpload.tsx` - New video upload component with drag & drop\n  - `components/CompressorSection.tsx` - New client wrapper for the compressor section\n  - `app/page.tsx` - Replaced placeholder anchor with CompressorSection\n- **Learnings:**\n  - Client components (`\"use client\"`) are needed for drag & drop and file input state management in Next.js App Router\n  - Wrapping interactive sections in a dedicated client component (CompressorSection) keeps the page.tsx as a server component\n  - The `SelectedFile` interface is exported for reuse by future components (US-005 compression input)\n  - Tailwind v4 custom colors work with opacity modifiers (e.g., `bg-accent/10`, `bg-accent/15`) out of the box\n  - Dual validation (MIME type + extension) handles edge cases where browsers report different MIME types for the same format\n---\n\n## 2026-02-17 - web-video-l39.5\n- Added target size input (MB) with validation to `CompressorSection`\n- Validations: minimum 1 MB, must be less than original file size, numeric input\n- Created API route `app/api/compress/route.ts` using `fluent-ffmpeg` for server-side compression\n- API route calculates video bitrate from target size and video duration (reserves 128kbps for audio)\n- Compression uses single-pass encoding with `-movflags +faststart` for web-optimized output\n- Added spinner animation on compress button during compression\n- Added animated progress bar indicator during compression\n- Error state with retry button and descriptive error messages\n- Success state shows compressed size vs original, download button, and \"compress another\" reset\n- Download generates descriptive filename (e.g., `video_compressed_9.00mb.mp4`)\n- Configured `next.config.ts` with `serverExternalPackages: [\"fluent-ffmpeg\"]` for proper server-side usage\n- Installed `fluent-ffmpeg` + `@types/fluent-ffmpeg` dependencies\n- **Files changed:**\n  - `components/CompressorSection.tsx` - Added target size input, compress button, progress, error/success states\n  - `app/api/compress/route.ts` - New API route for server-side FFmpeg compression\n  - `next.config.ts` - Added `serverExternalPackages` for fluent-ffmpeg\n  - `package.json` - Added fluent-ffmpeg dependency and @types/fluent-ffmpeg dev dependency\n- **Learnings:**\n  - `fluent-ffmpeg` is deprecated but still functional; it's the most common Node.js FFmpeg wrapper\n  - Next.js App Router API routes use `formData()` on the request to handle file uploads natively (no body-parser config needed)\n  - `serverExternalPackages` in next.config.ts is needed to prevent Next.js from bundling native/CLI-dependent packages like fluent-ffmpeg\n  - Bitrate calculation: `videoBitrate = (targetSizeBytes * 8 - audioBitrate * duration) / duration` — must subtract audio bits from total budget\n  - Streaming response with `ReadableStream` from `createReadStream` works well for returning large files from API routes\n  - Custom headers like `X-Compressed-Size` can be read client-side from `response.headers.get()` for metadata about the result\n---\n\n## 2026-02-17 - web-video-l39.3\n- Created `Features` component (`components/Features.tsx`) with 4 feature cards in a responsive grid\n- Features: sin límite de tamaño, todos los formatos, tamaño exacto, 100% gratis\n- Each card has an inline SVG icon (Heroicons), title, and description\n- Cards use dark theme: `bg-surface`, `border-border`, hover to `bg-surface-hover`/`border-border-hover`\n- Icon container uses `bg-accent/10` with `text-accent-light` for purple accent\n- Responsive grid: 1 col mobile, 2 col `sm`, 4 col `lg`\n- Updated `app/page.tsx` to render Features between Hero and CompressorSection\n- **Files changed:**\n  - `components/Features.tsx` - New features/benefits section component\n  - `app/page.tsx` - Added Features import and rendering\n- **Learnings:**\n  - Inline SVGs from Heroicons work cleanly in React/Next.js without extra dependencies\n  - The existing theme palette (`surface`, `border`, `accent/10`, `accent-light`) provides all needed tokens for card components\n---\n\n## 2026-02-17 - web-video-l39.6\n- US-006 (Download of compressed video) was already fully implemented during US-005 iteration\n- All acceptance criteria verified as present in `components/CompressorSection.tsx`:\n  - Download button visible after compression (line 269-275)\n  - Descriptive filename: `{baseName}_compressed_{sizeMB}mb.mp4` (line 72)\n  - Compressed file size displayed with comparison to original (lines 259-266)\n  - \"Comprimir otro\" reset button resets all state (lines 276-282, handleReset)\n- Quality gates pass: `pnpm typecheck` and `pnpm lint` both succeed\n- **Files changed:** None (already complete)\n- **Learnings:**\n  - US-005 implemented download functionality as part of the compression flow, making US-006 a no-op\n  - The `handleDownload` pattern using `URL.createObjectURL` + programmatic `<a>` click is the standard browser download approach\n---\n\n## 2026-02-17 - web-video-l39.7\n- Created FAQ accordion component (`components/FAQ.tsx`) with 6 collapsible questions\n- Questions cover: formatos soportados, límites de tamaño, privacidad, calidad, formato de salida, necesidad de cuenta\n- Smooth expand/collapse animation using CSS `grid-rows-[0fr]`/`grid-rows-[1fr]` trick with `transition-all`\n- Chevron icon rotates 180° on open with `transition-transform`\n- Single-open behavior (clicking one closes the previously open item)\n- Dark theme consistent: `bg-surface`, `border-border`, `hover:bg-surface-hover`\n- Updated `app/page.tsx` to render FAQ between CompressorSection and future Footer\n- **Files changed:**\n  - `components/FAQ.tsx` - New FAQ accordion component\n  - `app/page.tsx` - Added FAQ import and rendering\n- **Learnings:**\n  - CSS `grid-rows-[0fr]`/`grid-rows-[1fr]` with `overflow-hidden` child is the cleanest pure-CSS accordion animation approach — no JS height measurement needed\n  - Tailwind v4 arbitrary values like `grid-rows-[0fr]` work seamlessly for this pattern\n  - `divide-y divide-border` on the container cleanly handles separator lines between accordion items\n---\n\n## 2026-02-17 - web-video-l39.8\n- Created Footer component (`components/Footer.tsx`) with minimalist design\n- Footer includes dynamic copyright year, privacy and contact links\n- Uses `border-t border-border` and `bg-surface/50` for subtle visual separation\n- Responsive layout: stacked on mobile, horizontal on desktop (`sm:flex-row`)\n- Updated `app/page.tsx` to render Footer outside `<main>` using a fragment wrapper\n- **Files changed:**\n  - `components/Footer.tsx` - New footer component\n  - `app/page.tsx` - Added Footer import and rendering, wrapped in fragment\n- **Learnings:**\n  - `bg-surface/50` (opacity modifier) creates a subtle background that differentiates the footer from the main content without being too prominent\n  - Footer is placed outside `<main>` for semantic HTML — it's a sibling, not a child of main content\n---\n","structuredPatch":[{"oldStart":158,"oldLines":3,"newStart":158,"newLines":31,"lines":["   - `bg-surface/50` (opacity modifier) creates a subtle background that differentiates the footer from the main content without being too prominent","   - Footer is placed outside `<main>` for semantic HTML — it's a sibling, not a child of main content"," ---","+","+## 2026-02-17 - web-video-l39.9","+- Implemented optional login with NextAuth.js v5 (Auth.js) using GitHub as OAuth provider","+- Created `auth.ts` root config file exporting `handlers`, `signIn`, `signOut`, `auth`","+- Created `app/api/auth/[...nextauth]/route.ts` API route for auth handlers","+- Created `components/SessionProvider.tsx` client wrapper for NextAuthSessionProvider","+- Created `components/Header.tsx` with login button (unauthenticated), avatar+name+logout (authenticated), and loading skeleton","+- Updated `app/layout.tsx` to wrap children with SessionProvider, added Header and `pt-14` padding for fixed header","+- Updated `next.config.ts` with `images.remotePatterns` for GitHub and Google avatar domains","+- Created `.env.local` with `AUTH_SECRET` and placeholder GitHub OAuth credentials","+- Compressor works without login — no auth gates on any compression functionality","+- **Files changed:**","+  - `auth.ts` - New NextAuth v5 root configuration with GitHub provider","+  - `app/api/auth/[...nextauth]/route.ts` - New API route for auth handlers","+  - `components/SessionProvider.tsx` - New client-side session provider wrapper","+  - `components/Header.tsx` - New header with login/logout and session state","+  - `app/layout.tsx` - Added SessionProvider, Header, and content padding","+  - `next.config.ts` - Added image remote patterns for avatar domains","+  - `.env.local` - Auth secrets and GitHub OAuth placeholders (gitignored)","+  - `package.json` / `pnpm-lock.yaml` - Added next-auth@5.0.0-beta.30","+- **Learnings:**","+  - `next-auth@beta` (v5) installs cleanly with pnpm on Next.js 16 without peer dep issues","+  - GitHub provider in Auth.js v5 auto-reads `AUTH_GITHUB_ID` and `AUTH_GITHUB_SECRET` environment variables — no explicit `clientId`/`clientSecret` config needed","+  - `SessionProvider` must be a client component wrapping the layout's children for `useSession` to work in child client components","+  - Fixed header with `backdrop-blur-md` and `bg-background/80` creates a clean glassmorphism effect over dark theme","+  - `pt-14` on content div compensates for the fixed header height (~56px)","+  - `next/image` requires `remotePatterns` config for external avatar URLs (GitHub: `avatars.githubusercontent.com`, Google: `lh3.googleusercontent.com`)","+---"]}],"userModified":false,"replaceAll":false}}
